com.magnet.android.mms.async

Class CallManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.magnet.android.mms.async.CallManager

  • public class CallManager
extends Object
    This class provides basic management for cache, queue, and reliable calls. All methods in this class are blocking methods.

      • cancelAllPendingCalls

        public int cancelAllPendingCalls()
        Cancel all pending reliable calls having an INIT, QUEUED, or EXECUTING state. All constraints in the QUEUED calls will be stopped.
        Returns:
        Number of pending reliable calls cancelled; -1 if there is an error.

      • cancelAllPendingCalls

        public int cancelAllPendingCalls(String queueName)
        Cancel all pending reliable calls having an INIT, QUEUED, or EXECUTING state in a queue. All constraints in the QUEUED calls will be stopped.
        Parameters:
        queueName - The queue name.
        Returns:
        Number of pending calls reliable cancelled; -1 if there is an error.

      • getAllCalls

        public Collection<Call<?>> getAllCalls(int types)
        Retrieve all reliable calls with the specified types. Pending calls have a state of INIT, QUEUED or EXECUTING, and done calls have a state of SUCCESS, FAILED or TIMEDOUT. This is a blocking method. The Call instances are the same instances returned by the asynchronous invocations. The returned objects reflect the most recent state of the call, and are independent of the call data sent with the intent for a callback. Ensure each returned object is not null before using it, as it is possible the call may have been disposed.
        Parameters:
        types - TYPE_ALL or TYPE_DONE_ONLY or TYPE_PENDING_ONLY
        Returns:
        A collection of all reliable calls with the specified types.

      • getAllCalls

        public Collection<Call<?>> getAllCalls(String queueName,
                              int types)
        Retrieve all reliable calls in a queue with the specified types. Pending calls have a state of INIT, QUEUED or EXECUTING, and done calls have a state of SUCCESS, FALIED or TIMEDOUT. This is a blocking method. The Call instances are the same instances returned by the asynchronous invocations. The returned objects reflect the most recent state of the call, and are independent of the call data sent with the intent for a callback. Ensure each returned object is not null before using it, as it is possible the call may have been disposed.
        Parameters:
        queueName - The queue name.
        types - TYPE_ALL or TYPE_DONE_ONLY or TYPE_PENDING_ONLY
        Returns:
        A collection of all reliable calls in a queue with the specified types.

      • getCall

        public <T> Call<T> getCall(String id)
        Retrieve a Call instance by its unique ID. Use this method for reliable calls only. This Call instance is the same instance returned by the asynchronous invocation. The returned object reflects the most recent state of the call, and is independent of the call data sent with the intent for a callback. Ensure the returned object is not null before using it, as it is possible the call may have been disposed.
        Parameters:
        id - A Call unique ID.
        Returns:
        A Call object, or null if the ID is invalid, the call is timed out, or the asynchronous call was done, which is defined as a cached result being obsoleted or overwritten by another invocation.

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Shortcut for calling cancelAllPendingCalls() and clearCache(),

      • run

        public void run()
        Triggers all non-empty thread queues to be awakened (if asleep) to re-attempt processing. If a queue is blocked by a constraint, and the back-end constraint changes state to allow operational flows that were previously blocked, call this method to wake up the call manager thread queues to re-attempt queue processing before the next schedule.
